Title: Get started with Apps in Microsoft Teams
Teams mobile
Description: In this tutorial video we introduce you to the world of Microsoft Teams, the main feature areas and capabilities you need to know as you start your journey with Teams! Discover quick tips and actions that aim to make it easy for you to learn and love Teams.

Title: Book appointments
Description: Learn how others are using the appointments feature right in Teams. Use it to manage your staff's availability, assign appointments, coordinate schedules, send reminders and capture important notes.

Title: 3 apps to use in chat
Description: This week, Weston Lander, part of the #MicrosoftTeams team shares three apps you can start using in chat, today. Each app lets you take action directly from your Teams chat to create tasks, request approvals, or send praise to your teammates. Like with every other #TeamsApp, you can also search for each one and add it to Teams through the App Store.

Title: Intro
Description: In this tutorial video we introduce you to the world of Microsoft Teams, the main feature areas and capabilities you need to know as you start your journey with Teams! Discover quick tips and actions that aim to make it easy for you to learn and love Teams.

Title: Meetings
Description: In this tutorial video, we introduce you to Meetings in #MicrosoftTeams. Meetings are designed to connect the flow of your work, beyond the time during your meeting, so you can prepare before meetings and follow up afterwards seamlessly.

Title: Manage your notifications
Description: Learn how others organize their notifications to ensure they always know when something needs their attention with fewer distractions.

Title: Chats
Description: In this tutorial video, we introduce you to Chat in Microsoft Teams. Chat is at the center of how you communicate in Teams. Learn how you can message someone or a group of people to share ideas, files or simply have light and fun conversations on the go.

Title: Organize your projects
Description: Learn how others bring their teams together to organize and follow up on project updates in Microsoft Teams. Create weekly meetings, centralize files and assign tasks from your preferred channel.

Title: Teams and Channels
Description: In this tutorial video we introduce you to Teams and Channels in Microsoft Teams. A Team is a broad group of people who work together to get something done, such as a major company initiative, specialized projects, or just for fun. Channels are for a specific area within the larger team, such as a channel for design, marketing, or budget to support a team's objective, where people can have focused conversations.

Title: Access your company intranet
Description: Learn how in Teams, you can customize an internal landing page for your organization to share news, relevant links, and important resources with your employees, in one central place

Title: Send an emoji, GIF or sticker
Meet with external guests
Description: Learn how others are using Teams to communicate with their customers, vendors, and external partners. Create, join and follow up on all your meetings with both your internal team and external guests
